<item>
            <title>[DERBY-2027] JUnit suite All crashes with OutOfMemoryError when running LobLengthTest</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2027</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The All suite crashes when running jdbcapi/LobLengthTest.&lt;br/&gt;
It is reasonable to believe the memory usage accumulates and that this test makes the memory usage too high.&lt;br/&gt;
Looking at the test, it uses a ~16 MB byte array.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This problem was reported on derby-dev: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Out-of-memory-error-when-running-JUnit-suite-t2549103.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Out-of-memory-error-when-running-JUnit-suite-t2549103.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>General, but default heap space size for the VM used matters.</environment>
        <key id="12354455">DERBY-2027</key>
